criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with Acute Decompensated Heart Failure diagnosis, filling the Framingham
             diagnostic criteria, hospitalized at campus Hospital das Clínicas of Ribeirão Preto.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Creatinine clearance <30 ml / min / 1.73 m²;

          -  Acute coronary syndrome;

          -  Stroke;

          -  Dementia;

          -  Severe cognitive impairment;

          -  Cancer;

          -  Decompensated diabetes mellitus;

          -  Severe liver disease;

          -  Septic shock or with clinical signs of sepsis;

          -  Chronic renal parenchymal disease prior to the start of the study;

          -  ADHF secondary to acute renal failure;

          -  Nutritional disorders or those who are unable to take oral intake because of vomiting,
             dysphagia or gastroenteritis.
